That's cool Bijinko.  I will probably move my lowby alt up to the moon soon to try to see it from the ground up.  And I think there are friendly trainers in Shadowhaven and the cat city.<br>
<br>
Yeah there is something cool about the new areas and the "unknown" - which is one of the reasons I am trying to avoid major spoilage and zone maps.<br>
<br>
On Sunday we did an awesome crawl out in <br>
The Deep.  Very cool to not know what leads where, what mobs to expect, etc.  At first it was kind of standard fare with a group of cleric, enchanter, mage, warrior, druid, and shaman.  Lot's of static mobs in clusters so without an FD puller the enchanter was pretty critical.  But eventually we got deeper in and found unmezzable mobs that we couldn't get single pulls on.  Cobee's pet ended up being 2nd assist ;)   - and frankly for a pet it tanks damn well.  We had to get pretty ghetto in our approach with the pet tanking and sharing ghetto mez duties among those who could root.  Every pull felt dangerous and there was that constant "what's around the corner" feeling.  <br>
<br>
Then eventually the tunnel we were in opened up on this incredible cavern...  wow, it was very cool.  And there was something about knowing that maybe no one had been there yet on this server =)  But really it's the fact that WE didn't know that added the thrill.<br>
